Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 142
S.P. 78 In Senate, January 14, 2025
Fees for Attempted Withdrawals Involving Insufficient Funds
Reference to the Committee on Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services
suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator LIBBY of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Senator: BERNARD of Aroostook.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 9-B MRSA ยง241, sub-ยง16 is enacted to read:
3 16. Prohibition on charging more than one fee for insufficient funds associated
4 with the same withdrawal transaction. A financial institution authorized to do business
5 in this State or a credit union authorized to do business in this State may not charge a
6 customer's account more than one fee for insufficient funds associated with the same
7 withdrawal transaction even if more than one withdrawal attempt is made.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill prohibits a financial institution or credit union from charging a customer's
1100 account more than one fee for insufficient funds associated with the same withdrawal
1111 transaction even if more than one withdrawal attempt is made.
